Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech at South Carolina State University, highlighting the importance of leadership and the role of young people in shaping the future of America. She encouraged the freshmen to embrace the opportunities and challenges they will face during their college years, emphasizing the importance of resilience and determination. Harris discussed various issues, including the need for leadership in growing the economy, addressing the climate crisis, and ensuring access to quality education and healthcare. She also touched on the importance of protecting voting rights, advocating for women's reproductive rights, and addressing gun violence. Harris urged the students to use their voices and vote to drive change, emphasizing that their votes are powerful tools for shaping the future of the country. The speech concluded with a call for unity and a reminder of the importance of working together to overcome the challenges facing the nation.